spring-data-ldap. spring data for spring ldap is part of the umbrella spring data project which aims to provide a familiar and consistent repository abstractions for new spring ldap.
python build reasonableness. pbr is a library that injects some useful and sensible default behaviors into your setuptools run.
geometrical mean. a mean that calculates the n-th root of the product of the numbers.

aws-global-accelerator. this tag should be used when the questions asked concern about the latency of data transferred between the user and their application when they want to leverage aws internal network and avoid internet hops and automatic failover.
elastic-network-interface. this tag shall be used for aws elastic network interface related questions
excel::writer::xslx. use this tag for question about the perl module excel::writer::xlsx.
web-vitals. for questions related to any of the web vitals metrics: https://web.dev/vitals/
runtime.exec. the runtime.exec() method allows java apps. to create a new os process.
caffeine-cache. a high-performance in-memory cache for java and other jvm languages.
protobuf 3. protocol buffers version 3 - a new language design that is not backward compatible with previous versions.
phony makefile targets. a phony makefile target is a target that is not associated with a file name. make would not search for the file and its timestamp.

geographic regions of the amazon cloud. amazon web services (aws) cloud services are provided in different named geographic locations called "regions". different regions often require different configurations and feature slightly different services.

homepage. a homepage of an html site is the default page loaded when requesting a directory path from a web server. it is commonly named `index.html`, but may have other suffixes, depending on the server-side language.
html5 clipboard api. the html5 clipboard api enables web applications to interact with the host clipboard.

minecraft-fabric. for questions related to creating modifications for minecraft using fabricmc, an unofficial minecraft modding api created and built using the java programming language. fabricmc uses the yarn mapping set and modifies minecraft using the spongepowered mixin library.
tuleap. tuleap is a free and open-source application lifecycle management tool.
balena. questions related to balena.io (formerly resin) iot fleet management software.
pydicom. pydicom is a pure python package for working with dicom files such as medical images, reports, and radiotherapy objects.
patentsview. patentsview is a visualization, data dissemination, and analysis platform that focuses on intellectual property (ip) data. use this tag for api calls to patentsview.org.
gpuimage. gpuimage is an open source ios, macos, and linux framework for gpu-based image and video processing.  ports of the framework exist for android and other platforms.
silkjs. silkjs is a command shell built on top of google's v8 javascript engine, highly optimized for server-side applications.

linearmodels. a python package which provides estimation and inference in some common linear models including panel data and instrumental variables estimators. for questions related to implementation or interpretation of a linearmodels estimator.
xml namespace declared with no prefix. xml namespace declared with no prefix, for example, `xmlns="some-uri-here"`.
a functional library for webgl. for questions about regl the library and its usage
playcanvas. playcanvas is an html5, javascript, webgl game engine
nivo-react. nivo is a react based charting library
alpine-package-keeper. for question related to installing packages on the alpine linux distribution via the alpine package keeper — or apk.
time4j. concerns questions directly related to the alternative date, time and interval library time4j.
fluxor. fluxor is an implementation of the redux pattern, and provides state-management functionality on top of blazor.
windbg. windbg is a user and kernel mode debugger for windows. it can be used to debug both native and managed code.
kemal. this is for questions regarding the kemal framework for the crystal language.
do not use. purpose unclear and current usage imbi. do not use. purpose unclear and current usage ambiguous.
seccomp. 'seccomp' is an abbreviation for secure computing mode, a facility built into modern linux kernels that can be used to constrain (irreversibly) what a program is allowed to do.
vsts - build and release task development. questions on extending the visual studio team services build and release management system through extensions and custom tasks.

ibm rational developer for i. ibm rational developer is a family of eclipse-based ides. this tag should only be used for questions specifically about the ibm rational developer for i, not for rational developer ides meant for other platforms.
power-virtual-agents. for questions building chatbots using microsoft power virtual agents and integrating with microsoft bot framework & other technologies.
pytextrank. use this tag for questions about installing or using the pytextrank package or help with its algorithms. do not use this tag for questions about other implementations of textrank.

macos-monterey. released in 2021, macos monterey (version 12.4) is the eighteenth major release of apple's operating system for macintosh computers. use this tag for questions relating to macos apis that are specific to this version, and also tag your question with [macos]. do not use this tag simply because you are running code on this operating system.
kucoin. for questions on the apis provided by the cryptocurrency exchange kucoin.

proxy. the es2015 proxy wraps another object and provides customisable behaviour for basic operations (such as accessing properties). use cases include providing default values for undefined properties, validating set actions and customising the way objects are iterated.
slimselect. slim select is a standalone, "advanced" dropdown to replace / improve the basic html select

html5-kickstart. html kickstart is a ultra–lean set of html5, css, and jquery (javascript) files, layouts, and elements designed to give you a headstart and save you a lot of hours on your next web project
auto-py-to-exe. auto py to exe is a .py to .exe converter using a simple graphical interface and pyinstaller in python.
pandas-styles. [pandas-styles] is to be used on questions about table visualization using pandas built-in styler object (df.style). be sure to also include the tag [pandas].

locks. a lock generally refers to something that prevents another process from starting or accessing the same information until the lock is released. use with an appropriate language tag. do not use for physical locks.
mobile-robot-toolkit. mobile robot programming toolkit (mrpt) is a c++ set of libraries and tools for working in robotics. use with the [c++] tag and any specific c++ version tags.

windows-11. microsoft windows version 11 is an operating system for computers. use for questions about software development on or for the os. general support questions are off-topic and may be asked on https://superuser.com

amazon polly. amazon polly is a text-to-speech (tts) cloud service that converts text into lifelike speech. amazon polly supports multiple languages and includes a variety of voices, to build speech-enabled applications that work in multiple locations and use the appropriate voice for customers.
aws x-ray. aws x-ray allows developers to analyze the behavior of distributed applications by providing request tracing, exception collection, and profiling capabilities.

actions-builder. the actions builder is a web-based ide that is built-into the actions on google console, allowing developers to create scenes, intents, types, and prompts for conversational actions. it includes the actions sdk, a command line tool allowing you to download, edit, and upload the configuration for the web-based builder.

wildfly-26. use this tag for version specific questions about wildfly 26 - the lightweight, managed application runtime. when using this tag also include the more generic [wildfly] tag where possible.
ant design - one design language for ui. ant design is a enterprise-class ui design language and react-based implementation.

underscore-java. underscore-java is a port of underscore.js for java. as such, consider also using the [java] tag.

luau. luau is a scripting language based on lua 5.1.
walrus-operator. the "walrus operator" is an informal term for the assignment expression syntax (a := b) that were proposed in pep 572 and introduced in python 3.8
xticks. for questions related to xticks in matplotlib, seaborn, or pandas plots.
jointplot. for plotting a jointplot in python or r, using seaborn or ggextra
typed racket. typed racket is a statically typed dialect of the racket scheme-derived language, that eases the migration from untyped to typed code.
cps. continuation-passing style. use tag [continuation-passing].
pipenv. for questions related to python's pipenv dependency management tool.

geturl is an ambiguous tag with different meanings. geturl can refer to a specific function in a library, api or framework. examples of geturl methods is found in curl, google places and powerbuilder.

geturl can also refer to the concept of programmatically retrieving an url (or part of a url) from a string a other resource.
mongodb-tools. the mongodb database tools are a collection of command-line utilities for working with a mongodb deployment.

collapse. this tag is deprecated and should not be used, because it lacks discriminating power.  
use a tag related to the library that the collapse function belongs to instead.
